history.content: Since I'm not managing enrollment for Data 100 this semester I can't answer your question directly. I recommend that you view the class on classes.berkeley.edu to see what the seating reserves are and if they are applying pre-requisites. I know that sometimes STAT will use the enrollment system to enforce pre-reqs which is different than how CompSci handles enrollments.

I am currently a CS-intended junior transfer (I will know after this semester after completing CS 70). So I'm trying to enroll in CS/Stat C100 and I followed what one of the posts said about enrolling as Stat C100. Apparently the class is full, but I wasn't able to find a waitlist option under enrollment preferences (I was able to for other classes). Can anyone advise? Is it closed for now?
